caption: Great space, intimate and quiet when you want to rest or zone out.
Lovely park for the kids.  Note it does not open until 8 am, which is important for the jet lagged.
A hidden gem of quiet in the city. A great place to find a bench and munch on a baguette (purchased elsewhere). Beware of the birds, they are particularly assertive if you have food.
Lovely place with lots of sunshine in the morning hours. Well maintained and clean.
It's nice for young aged children if you can keep an eye on them. Depending on the hour this place can be badly attended. Not nearly as good as other parcs in the area. No big lawns, no restrooms.
Small beautiful park.
Nice little park in Saint Augustin area.
Peaceful square in the middle of the busy 8th arrondissement. Great to seat and read a book.
Good place. Nice.
Peaceful space in the middle of the city, Ping pong table. Googled Pagnol and was surprised how well I knew this novelist
It's good to walk in this area around the place here at Miromesnil there is a lot of beautiful spots near Paris Sainte Lazare
Nice small square with a ping pong table. Very close to Saint Lazare.
Vey green, calm and beautiful square.
A pigeon stole my wallet, dangerous park
Cute lil parc
Quiet and peaceful place
You can also play ping pong
Nice park

Very nice public park with trees and plants. It has several areas to rest, hang out or have a quiet conversation. It has a children's play area with slides and sand. Charming place.
Pretty little square with plenty of trees, plenty of benches to take a break. A small children's play area.

Pretty square with trees, plants and flowers located near the Saint Augustin church. Pleasant to go to, for all ages. You can stroll there, have lunch there, play there or simply take a break. And you can see all kinds of birds there, including robins if you are a keen observer! To visit.
Pretty little park in the heart of Paris Pleasant to sit, rest, read or have lunch
The little square is really cute, and ideal for reading a book.
Small square (1867) with plenty of trees, located between the Cercle Militaire and the Cosem Miromesnil.
Peaceful square near Saint Lazare. Perfect for spending a little moment of relaxation during the lunch break or to relax with friends and chat. Many benches are available.
Very nice park. The ping table needs to be renovated!! Wobbly net!
A green space a stone‚Äôs throw from St Augustin. A paradise for birds and children. A ping pong table available. Be careful of lots of rats „Äã avoid lawns!
a super quiet, and very beautiful park

Very nice place next to the Maritime Museum whose building has been redone. This place is calm with beautiful rose beds, benches to allow the elderly and parents to sit. Children have plenty of space for games. There is a fountain and quiet places to rest and get some fresh air.

We were looking for a quiet, pleasant and easily accessible place to eat our lunch and we were served! The park is well maintained, there are plenty of benches to sit and enjoy the good weather, there are also events like the garden festival. It's a fairly busy place because there were students, children, parents, people who, exactly like us, were taking a little lunch break üòäüëç We also discovered the Saint-Augustin church of Jeanne D'arc which is beautiful right next to the park. Ps: pay attention to pedestrian crossings to access it because, due to the works, there are no traffic lights.
Nice when it's not raining because there is no covered place in the park. I work nearby sometimes I take my break here.

When the weather is good, the well-kept park invites you to take a break on the lawn or on benches. It is a small and beautiful oasis in the city and is popular with students and some parents with children. I liked it there.

Very pretty park, well maintained, with a view of the St. Augustin church. And a ping pong table in the middle. The only drawbacks are the bird droppings on some benches and the trash cans next to them, not ideal when you're on a lunch break.

This square is very interesting because it is not very well known and has many white spaces and a few places on the lawn for those who venture there. In summer it is a place very popular with students and relatively unknown to employees in the surrounding offices. I recommend it to eat your sandwich and drink your little Badoit fresh from the first rays of sun :-)
Great little square, great for taking a break while waiting for a train at St Lazare station, several benches in the shade, greenery, trash cans, it's perfect! Thank you Paris üòä ‚Ä¶
A pretty little green square, with benches to rest on and a few ping pong tables. Very good for resting in the 8th district, a short lunch break...
